    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Nothing much to expect guys. This is my first blog post using octopress. If you don&rsquo;t know about octopress, it&rsquo;s a blogging framework for hackers. Today, I&rsquo;m going to explore the plugins of Octopress.</p>

<p>To test the plugins, I&rsquo;ll use them in this post directly. Here we go.</p>

<h3>Excerpts</h3>

<p>The plugin allows you to display only a small portion of the post and add a &ldquo;read more&rdquo; link. For that, i need to use a <code>&lt;!&mdash;more&mdash;&gt;</code> tag in the content. Let&rsquo;s try it out. <!--more--></p>

<p>If you saw a link that says &ldquo;Read On&rdquo;, the excerpts plugin is working.</p>

<h3>HTML5 Video Tag</h3>

<p>Next is HTML5 Video Tag. To try this, I&rsquo;m gonna use the video of sintel. One of my favorite independent films.
Unfortunately, the video is not working for me. It looks like an outdated plugin. Btw, you can watch the movie @ <a href="http://www.sintel.org">www.sintel.org</a>.
